<HEADLINE>
FT  01 JAN 94 / International Company News: Upjohn faces Dollars 1bn lawsuit
over Halcion
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FRANK MCGURTY
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Upjohn, the US pharmaceuticals group, said yesterday it was named in a
lawsuit filed on behalf of five people who had allegedly suffered severe
side-effects from using Halcion, a sleeping medication banned in the UK but
widely prescribed elsewhere.
The company said it was unaware of the details of the lawsuit, which is
seeking Dollars 1bn in damages, according to The Houston Chronicle.
The suit contends that Upjohn relied on falsified clinical studies to win
approval of the medication by the US Food and Drug Administration, according
to the report.
Declining comment on the lawsuit, the company defended Halcion as 'very safe
and effective' when used as directed.
