<HEADLINE>
FT  01 JAN 94 / World Stock Markets: South Africa
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A becalmed gold price and strong financial rand took the sparkle off
Johannesburg.
Gold shares paused after Thursday's rally although good demand continuedfor
second-tier industrials. Golds shed 12 to 2,164, while industrials rose 11
to a record 5,573. The overall index gained 4 to 4,893. Barlows lost 50
cents to R54.75 while Anglos added R2 to a new high of R219.50.
