<HEADLINE>
FT  01 JAN 94 / International Company News: Italian steel group sells
subsidiary
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By HAIG SIMONIAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MILAN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Ilva, the heavily loss-making Italian steel group, has made a further step
towards its dismemberment and privatisation with the sale of its Cogne
special steels unit.
Cogne, which specialises in stainless steel products, has been bought by
Marzorati, a private steel group based in the Ticino region of Switzerland.
No price for the transaction, reported by the Ansa news agency, has been
revealed and Ilva was unavailable for comment yesterday.
The Cogne subsidiary is one of a number of Ilva assets for sale as part of
the group's restructuring plan. Under the scheme, Ilva has been broken up
into separate companies, all of which are to be privatised.
</TEXT>
